Transport fare paid by passengers for bus, air, motorcycle and waterway journeys rose month-on-month (MoM)  in July despite the decline in the price of Premium Motor Spirit, PMS, also known as petrol, during the period. <img class="aligncenter  wp-image-1226598" src="https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/road-transport.jpg?resize=640%2C391&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="640" height="391" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/road-transport.jpg?w=1500&amp;ssl=1 1500w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/road-transport.jpg?resize=300%2C183&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/road-transport.jpg?resize=768%2C469&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/road-transport.jpg?resize=1024%2C625&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/road-transport.jpg?resize=58%2C35&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/road-transport.jpg?resize=260%2C159&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/road-transport.jpg?resize=200%2C122&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/road-transport.jpg?resize=560%2C342&amp;ssl=1 560w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/road-transport.jpg?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> According to the latest PMS report by the National Bureau of Statistics’ (NBS), average price paid by consumers for PMS decreased by 1.2 percent year-on-year (YoY) and 0.2 percent MoM to N145.0 in July 2019 from N145.4 in June 2019.” Meanwhile, NBS’  latest Transport   Fare Watch report showed that the fare  paid by passengers for bus journey within the city increased by 7.06 percent to N195.76 in July 2019 from N182.84 in June 2019 while fare paid by commuters for bus journey intercity increased by 0.76 percent to N1,619.05   in July 2019 from   N1,606.92 in June 2019. The report further showed that the fare paid by air passengers for specified routes single journey increased by 0.32 percent to N30,562.97 in July 2019 from N30,464.86 in June 2019 while fare paid for journey by motorcycle (Okada) per drop increased by 1.38 percent to N118.62 in July 2019 from N117.00 in June 2019. READ ALSO: Why the price of Kerosene is high – NNPC It further stated that fare paid by passengers for water way passenger transport increased by 9.05 percent to N550.89 in July 2019 from N505.18 in June 2019. Prices of rice, others drop Meanwhile, the prices of rice, tomatoes, agric egg and yam declined in July, according to the “Selected Food Price Watch” report for July also released yesterday by NBS The report stated: “The average price of one dozen of Agric eggs medium size decreased year-on-year by 0.73 percent and MoM by 5.45 percent to N468.31 in July 2019 from N495.32 in June 2019 while the average price of piece of Agric eggs medium size (price of one) decreased YoY by 6.88 per cent and MoM by 2.35 per cent to N38.38 in July 2019 from N39.31 in June 2019. “The average price of one kg of tomato decreased YoY by 39.47 per cent and MoM by 9.96 per cent to N203.55 in July 2019 from N226.07 in June 2019. VANGUARD Despite the decline in the price of premium motor spirit (PMS) also known as petrol, the average fare paid by passengers for bus journey intercity, air journey and journey by motorcycle increased month-on-month (MoM) in April 2019. May 21, 2019 In "Business" The average fare paid by passengers for bus journey within city rose slightly by 0.26 percent month-on-month (MoM) to N182.84 in June 2019 from N182.37 in May 2019. July 19, 2019 In "Business" AVERAGE price paid for Premium Motor Spirit (PMS), otherwise known as petrol last month decreased year-on-year (YoY) by 1.9 percent and 2.5 percent month-on-month (MoM) to N144.4 from N148.2 in July 2017, according to the latest report by the Nigerian Bureau of Statistics (NBS). September 18, 2017 In "Business"